1.70_09 2017-05-13T13:04:51+02:00 (f12c93d => abeltje)
 - (abeltje) Do not die() on using for non-Windows
 -     This helps the Pod::Coverage test
 -     lower_error_setting() now just returns on non-Windows

 - (abeltje) Cleanup Test::Smoke::Util::Win32ErrorMode and add a test for
   it.

 - (abeltje) Fix broken test for MSWin32
 -     Implement 'cat' in perl, so it will work for all osses.

 - (abeltje) Add new MSWin32 log message in the test

 - (abeltje) Merge branch 'rt/39138' of
   ssh://source.test-smoke.org:9999/~/Test-Smoke into rt/39138

 - (abeltje) Fix Test::Smoke::App::RunSmoke and test.
 -     'is_win32' is not an attribute, but a config-item.
 -     use '$0' and not hard coded test name.

 - (abeltje) Fix poster-post.t on Windows.
 -     fork() and JSON::XS don't work together on Windows; For this test we
   enforce the use of JSON::PP as a backend for JSON.

 - (abeltje) Fix Test::Smoke::App::RunSmoke and test.
 -     'is_win32' is not an attribute, but a config-item.
 -     use '$0' and not hard coded test name.

 - (abeltje) Change the Win32-ErrorSettings for this process
 -     This is an old patch provided by Jan Dubois in RT-39138

