1.70_01 2016-05-22T12:48:48+02:00 (92616c2 => abeltje)
 - (abeltje) Rework of Andy Grundman's patch to split rsync options
 -     Use shellwords($args) rather than split(" ", $args) to split the
 -     configured options to rsync(1)
 -     Thanks Andy!

 - (Andy Grundman) Split rsync arguments that are combined into one string,
   such as the default '-az --delete'.

 - (Andy Grundman) Revert previous change, breaks args where spaces are
   expected

 - (Andy Grundman) Split arguments that might be combined into one string,
   such as the rsync default '-az --delete'.

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Skip testing git that does not support "git init
   folder"
 -     There might be a higher bound than this, but at least git-1.6.4.2
   does
 -     NOT support this syntax
 -     usage: git init [-q | --quiet] [--bare]
   [--template=<template-directory>] [--shared[=<permissions>]]

