1.61_02 2014-08-22T14:33:51+03:00 (89d1c23 => Abe Timmerman)
 - (Abe Timmerman) New machine

 - (abetim) Add files to the MANIFEST

 - (abetim) Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master' into Lyon2014
 -     Conflicts:
 -	   lib/Test/Smoke/Reporter.pm

 - (abetim) Pull SysInfo.pm from master.

 - (Abe Timmerman) Fix nonfatalmessage()

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Documentation for AIX OS version
 -     "oslevel -s" output may say the system is older than it actually is.
 -     It by default reports the most recent consistent level. If a single
 -     fileset is missing  (for example /usr/include files)  at the latest
 -     level, the old level is reported rather than the level of "most" of
 -     the system.
 -     $ oslevel -s
 -     6100-09-03-1415
 -     $ oslevel -q -s | head -3
 -     Known Service Packs
 -     -------------------
 -     6100-09-03-1415
 -     6100-09-02-1412
 -     6100-09-01-1341
 -     The RD seems to be important for finding filesets:
 -     bos:bos.rte.install:6.1.9.16: : :C:F:LPP Install Commands: : : : : :
   :0:0:/:1415

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) AIX OS version analysis updated
 -     As of AIX 5.3/ML05, the new "oslevel -s" will output the OS version
   in
 -     4 parts: OS version, TL (previous ML), SP and release date

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Typo in instruction

 - (H.Merijn Brand) We do not want to see failing patch --version output
 -     This is exactly why we do the test
 -     t/patcher.t ...................... 1/41
   /data/data/com.pdaxrom.cctools/root/cctools/bin/patch: unrecognized
   option '--version'
 -     BusyBox v1.21.1 (2013-12-08 10:51:29 EET) multi-call binary.
 -     Usage: patch [OPTIONS] [ORIGFILE [PATCHFILE]]
 -	   -p N    Strip N leading components from file names
 -	   -i DIFF Read DIFF instead of stdin
 -	   -R	   Reverse patch
 -	   -N	   Ignore already applied patches
 -	   -E	   Remove output files if they become empty

 - (H.Merijn Brand) Guard against warnings for negative repeat in
   pad-length
 -     RT#96821 - "Negative repeat count does nothing" warnings
 -     https://rt.cpan.org/Ticket/Display.html?id=96821
 -     Negative repeat count does nothing at
   /data/data/home/.cpan/build/Test-Smoke-1.6-sou720/blib/lib/Test/Smoke/Reporter.pm
   line 1097.

 - (H.Merijn Brand) no else after return

 - (H.Merijn Brand) Prevent false negatives in CPU speed report

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) The newer gcc:s seem to have also "note: ..."
   (jhi)

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) map g++ warnings to gcc (jhi)

 - (H.Merijn Brand) Forgot to rename DSM dist files in MANIFEST

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) NetBSD release info
 -     they *only* have /etc/release
 -     I don't know if that is valid for all NetBSD releases

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) tests for DSM called dsm, not ds213

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) DSM-5.0 & DSM-4.3
 -     With DSM, dist-detection will find two files named VERSION
 -     The first it finds is the newest. Previous test had the wrong
 -     stored in t/etc/ds213-4.3

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Oracle Linux Server

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Add sysinfo for RHEL-6.4

 - (Abe Timmerman) Merge branch 'master' of
   ssh://github.com/abeltje/Test-Smoke

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) add RHEL server distro names

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) typo in verbose tests

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) shorten long name
 -     Do not use the word "release" in destro name

 - (Abe Timmerman) Rewrite grepnonfatal() to use the file-contents rather
   than the file-name.

 - (Abe Timmerman) Rewrite grepccmsg() so it takes the file-contents rather
   than the file-name.

 - (Abe Timmerman) Small refectornig, read_logfile() is a utility function,
   Test::Smoke::Reporter->get_log() is the method.

 - (Abe Timmerman) Add -vtype switch to influence the type of version-bump
   you want.

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Newer Test::More requires (not use's)
   Scalar::Util

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Keep the "wide character" logs
 -     {"db_error":"Wide character in subroutine entry at
   ../perl5/lib/perl5//JSON.pm line 171.\n","error":"Unexpected error."}
 -     => Dancer problem

 - (Abe Timmerman) Refactor Test::Smoke::Poster->post() for easier logging.

 - (abeltje) Fix test for systems that have either JSON::XS or JSON::PP
   installed.

 - (abeltje) Fix checking of ExtUtils::MakeMaker->VERSION (some people have
   "_-versions" installed.

 - (Abe Timmerman) Merge branch 'master' of
   ssh://github.com/abeltje/Test-Smoke

 - (Abe Timmerman) Fix check for usable JSON module.

 - (Abe Timmerman) Provide more (up to date) information for Windows, fix
   tests.

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Fix synology distname detection

 - (Abe Timmerman) Merge branch 'master' of
   ssh://github.com/abeltje/Test-Smoke

 - (H.Merijn Brand - Tux) Add meta-info for repository
 -     BTW hccnet.nl is long dead and gone

 - (Abe Timmerman) Merge branch 'Lyon2014'

 - (Abe Timmerman) Fix some test issues:
 -	 - Document constants
 -	 - Suppress output from git clone
 -	 - Add comment to a test

